This paper is about certifying the robustness of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a probabilistic approach for certifying the robustness of neural networks, which involves analyzing the distributional characteristics of the input perturbations. This work is likely to be relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and neural networks (cs.NE). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as they are the most closely related to the topic of machine learning and neural networks.
